19
00:01:59,551 --> 00:02:02,640
My masters are only
the viscount and you, Ms. Malai.

20
00:02:03,051 --> 00:02:05,911
You're the only lady
of this house, Ms. Malai.

21
00:02:10,230 --> 00:02:11,230
You ingrate!

22
00:02:11,241 --> 00:02:13,240
Admit you wanna be
the master of this house!

23
00:02:13,489 --> 00:02:14,710
That's not true, my lord.

24
00:02:15,757 --> 00:02:16,523
My lord!

25
00:02:16,717 --> 00:02:17,757
See, Malai?

26
00:02:17,949 --> 00:02:19,636
I told you Dech was the murderer.

27
00:02:20,117 --> 00:02:21,440
- Ms. Malai!
- Let Dech go!

28
00:02:24,637 --> 00:02:25,664
Ramphoei.

29
00:02:34,350 --> 00:02:35,423
Wait a minute.

30
00:02:37,490 --> 00:02:39,490
Why don't you take Dech with you?

31
00:02:40,430 --> 00:02:42,203
You have a strong
eyewitness statement.

32
00:02:42,483 --> 00:02:44,483
Two witnesses
give different accounts.

33
00:02:44,517 --> 00:02:46,617
We could be punished
if we arrest him.

34
00:02:47,190 --> 00:02:48,596
We can't do it unless

35
00:02:48,710 --> 00:02:50,710
there's clear evidence, my lord.

36
00:02:51,030 --> 00:02:53,400
You can't believe the words
of a woman like Ramphoei.

37
00:02:53,883 --> 00:02:55,710
And they both benefit
from his death.

38
00:02:56,103 --> 00:02:58,770
Uan's statement
has more weight, isn't it?

39
00:02:59,143 --> 00:03:00,856
It's not that simple, my lord.

40
00:03:01,073 --> 00:03:03,640
If there's no clear evidence
that Dech did it,

41
00:03:03,797 --> 00:03:05,040
there's nothing we can do.

42
00:03:06,797 --> 00:03:08,480
We'll take our leave, my lord.

43
00:03:21,570 --> 00:03:22,570
My lord!

44
00:03:22,581 --> 00:03:23,608
My lord!

45
00:03:24,143 --> 00:03:25,143
My lord!

46
00:03:25,483 --> 00:03:26,483
My lord!

47
00:03:28,157 --> 00:03:29,357
I'm begging you.

48
00:03:30,503 --> 00:03:31,836
Please believe me.

49
00:03:32,203 --> 00:03:33,350
I really didn't do it.

50
00:03:33,537 --> 00:03:34,537
I don't believe you!

51
00:03:35,780 --> 00:03:38,520
You dare have an affair
with my brother's mistress.

52
00:03:39,053 --> 00:03:40,560
You could do worse things.

53
00:03:41,093 --> 00:03:42,093
Who knows?

54
00:03:42,686 --> 00:03:44,970
You might have always
planned to kill my brother!

55
00:03:45,180 --> 00:03:47,180
But I never planned
to hurt the viscount.

56
00:03:47,513 --> 00:03:48,513
Stop pretending.

57
00:03:48,827 --> 00:03:49,827
Someday

58
00:03:50,013 --> 00:03:51,880
I'll rip off your mask, Dech.

59
00:03:52,583 --> 00:03:54,560
People like you
should die in prison!

60
00:03:54,877 --> 00:03:55,997
Mark my words!

61
00:03:56,517 --> 00:03:57,517
Let's go, Ranchuan.

62
00:03:58,023 --> 00:03:59,440
- Yes, my lord.
- My lord!

63
00:04:00,897 --> 00:04:01,897
My lord!

64
00:04:25,530 --> 00:04:26,730
Ms. Malai, I...

65
00:04:47,923 --> 00:04:48,923
Ms. Malai!

66
00:05:14,543 --> 00:05:17,396
You believe Ms. Ramphoei's words?

67
00:05:18,197 --> 00:05:19,557
If I don't believe her,

68
00:05:21,090 --> 00:05:22,560
then Dech's the murderer.

69
00:05:25,070 --> 00:05:26,640
But if I do...

70
00:05:34,283 --> 00:05:36,383
I don't wanna believe
anyone anymore, Fueang.

71
00:05:49,597 --> 00:05:51,310
I don't wanna believe it either

72
00:05:52,057 --> 00:05:54,057
that Dech could kill the viscount.

73
00:05:54,297 --> 00:05:55,957
And I don't believe...

74
00:05:56,970 --> 00:05:58,737
that he would cheat on you.

75
00:06:01,670 --> 00:06:04,360
Why don't you give him
another chance?

76
00:06:05,870 --> 00:06:08,283
I don't wanna hear anyone's
excuses anymore, Fueang.

77
00:06:11,070 --> 00:06:13,403
The more I hear them,
the stupider I feel.

78
00:06:17,003 --> 00:06:19,003
Go oversee things downstairs.

79
00:06:21,270 --> 00:06:22,270
Yes, ma'am.

80
00:07:35,683 --> 00:07:36,683
Dech.

81
00:07:39,610 --> 00:07:40,960
What's going on, Kam, Uan?

82
00:07:41,670 --> 00:07:42,670
Well,

83
00:07:42,823 --> 00:07:44,929
I wanted to apologize
for giving that statement.

84
00:07:45,397 --> 00:07:46,590
- But...
- I get it.

85
00:07:48,103 --> 00:07:49,320
Do you really?

86
00:07:50,623 --> 00:07:53,010
I don't want you to think
we tried to frame you.

87
00:07:54,310 --> 00:07:56,637
Yes, I really didn't try
to frame you.

88
00:07:57,183 --> 00:07:59,643
We just didn't want
to lie to the police.

89
00:07:59,763 --> 00:08:00,763
I know.

90
00:08:00,977 --> 00:08:02,360
You're really not mad at us?

91
00:08:02,857 --> 00:08:04,057
Why would I be?

92
00:08:04,417 --> 00:08:06,024
You just told them what you saw.

93
00:08:07,670 --> 00:08:09,000
We're gonna go back to work.

94
00:08:41,637 --> 00:08:43,244
Just say what you want, ma'am.

95
00:08:45,317 --> 00:08:46,320
Gee,

96
00:08:46,583 --> 00:08:48,280
you read my mind.

97
00:08:48,710 --> 00:08:52,680
I thought I had to remind you
to repay my kindness.

98
00:08:52,943 --> 00:08:55,983
You'd never help me without
expecting something in return.

99
00:08:57,843 --> 00:08:59,843
Tell me how much you want, ma'am.

100
00:09:02,403 --> 00:09:03,403
Goodness.

101
00:09:03,976 --> 00:09:05,630
You're so innocent.

102
00:09:06,863 --> 00:09:08,917
I went out of my way to help you.

103
00:09:09,397 --> 00:09:10,630
If it weren't for me,

104
00:09:10,877 --> 00:09:13,520
you would have been
in jail right now.

105
00:09:13,837 --> 00:09:16,177
How can you repay me
with just cash?

106
00:09:18,583 --> 00:09:20,320
Then what do you want, ma'am?

107
00:09:27,097 --> 00:09:28,657
I'm not asking much.

108
00:09:29,017 --> 00:09:30,324
I just want to...

109
00:09:31,720 --> 00:09:32,920
Don't cross the line.

110
00:09:33,096 --> 00:09:34,280
I can give you some things.

111
00:09:34,490 --> 00:09:35,920
Not everything.

112
00:09:40,570 --> 00:09:42,426
What if I'm telling you...

113
00:09:42,437 --> 00:09:44,600
I want everything?

114
00:09:45,930 --> 00:09:47,483
Then you might get nothing.

115
00:09:48,283 --> 00:09:49,520
Not a damn thing.

116
00:09:54,757 --> 00:09:56,560
Aren't you a little too sure?

117
00:09:57,280 --> 00:09:58,370
Don't forget.

118
00:09:58,843 --> 00:10:01,320
I just prevented
your incarceration.

119
00:10:30,157 --> 00:10:31,330
You called me, ma'am?

120
00:10:31,997 --> 00:10:34,880
Uan, take Mueang to the wet nurse.

121
00:10:39,957 --> 00:10:41,560
That's Ms. Malai's necklace, ma'am.

122
00:10:42,570 --> 00:10:43,600
Oh.

123
00:10:43,870 --> 00:10:45,563
You don't have
the right to wear it.

124
00:10:45,903 --> 00:10:46,903
Give it here.

125
00:10:47,270 --> 00:10:48,680
None of your business.

126
00:10:49,137 --> 00:10:51,403
I'm the viscount's mistress.
Why can't I wear it?

127
00:10:51,583 --> 00:10:52,850
Even so,

128
00:10:53,030 --> 00:10:55,030
no one wears diamonds to funerals.

129
00:10:55,330 --> 00:10:56,950
People will say you...

130
00:10:56,997 --> 00:10:58,744
don't know the time and place.

131
00:10:59,029 --> 00:11:01,029
Uan, are you criticizing me?

132
00:11:01,190 --> 00:11:02,440
I'm telling the truth.

133
00:11:02,843 --> 00:11:04,457
Ms. Malai wears only pearls.

134
00:11:04,783 --> 00:11:06,943
She wouldn't flash diamonds
in people's eyes.

135
00:11:06,997 --> 00:11:08,743
Jeez, screw your eyes.

136
00:11:08,850 --> 00:11:09,880
I'm gonna wear it.

137
00:11:10,623 --> 00:11:13,800
Take Mueang to the wet nurse
already. He's so annoying.

138
00:11:14,023 --> 00:11:15,160
Go away already.

139
00:11:15,483 --> 00:11:16,520
Yes, ma'am.

140
00:11:17,877 --> 00:11:19,017
Young Master Mueang,

141
00:11:19,703 --> 00:11:20,703
let's go, sir.

142
00:11:23,470 --> 00:11:24,470
Let's go, sir.

143
00:11:37,763 --> 00:11:39,560
Please accept my condolences,
Ms. Malai.

144
00:11:40,750 --> 00:11:41,750
Thank you.

145
00:11:42,230 --> 00:11:44,880
I never thought the viscount
would pass away so young.

146
00:11:52,990 --> 00:11:54,004
Hello.

147
00:11:54,563 --> 00:11:56,003
Thank you for coming.

148
00:11:57,176 --> 00:11:59,433
- Goodness.
- Tell me if you need anything.

149
00:11:59,444 --> 00:12:00,920
At her own husband's funeral.

150
00:12:01,243 --> 00:12:03,516
How could she wear
such flashy jewelry?

151
00:12:05,263 --> 00:12:06,310
People's pedigree

152
00:12:06,797 --> 00:12:08,040
cannot be changed.

153
00:12:08,710 --> 00:12:10,960
It must be so hard for you
to share a house

154
00:12:11,277 --> 00:12:12,517
with someone like that.

155
00:12:14,130 --> 00:12:16,130
I have to apologize for her.

156
00:12:16,643 --> 00:12:17,880
Don't worry, Ms. Malai.

157
00:12:18,577 --> 00:12:19,680
I understand.

158
00:12:20,830 --> 00:12:21,960
Uh...

159
00:12:22,050 --> 00:12:23,697
Then make yourself at home.

160
00:12:24,310 --> 00:12:25,603
- Yes.
- Yes.

161
00:12:26,577 --> 00:12:28,160
I feel horrible, ma'am.

162
00:12:37,717 --> 00:12:40,077
Is it a good idea for you to skip

163
00:12:40,203 --> 00:12:41,236
the viscount's funeral?

164
00:12:42,417 --> 00:12:45,564
I know it looks bad, not attending
my own brother's funeral.

165
00:12:46,163 --> 00:12:48,744
But I don't want Malai
to receive guests by herself.

166
00:12:49,057 --> 00:12:50,640
I feel for Malai

167
00:12:50,990 --> 00:12:53,650
but I don't want to curse myself
by stepping in that house.

168
00:12:53,990 --> 00:12:56,080
Especially with Dech
and Ramphoei there,

169
00:12:56,329 --> 00:12:58,943
we'd surely cause a scene
and become the talk of the town.

170
00:12:59,450 --> 00:13:00,570
It's better I don't go.

171
00:13:09,790 --> 00:13:11,960
Oh, Count. Hello, my lord.

172
00:13:13,436 --> 00:13:14,436
I'm sorry.

173
00:13:15,710 --> 00:13:17,117
I never thought

174
00:13:17,600 --> 00:13:19,880
the viscount would
pass away so soon.

175
00:13:22,020 --> 00:13:23,520
Our son's still a baby.

176
00:13:24,410 --> 00:13:25,800
My dear Mueang,

177
00:13:26,530 --> 00:13:27,880
he's fatherless

178
00:13:28,010 --> 00:13:29,600
at such a young age.

179
00:13:35,657 --> 00:13:36,960
Oh, milady.

180
00:13:38,623 --> 00:13:39,840
Hello, ma'am.

181
00:13:55,283 --> 00:13:56,640
Even though you're gone,

182
00:13:56,923 --> 00:14:00,030
I'll never let my child
become your heir.

183
00:14:00,850 --> 00:14:01,850
Ever.

184
00:14:07,837 --> 00:14:09,360
Why did you say that?

185
00:14:14,043 --> 00:14:16,043
No matter how much you hated him,

186
00:14:17,010 --> 00:14:18,600
you shouldn't have said that.

187
00:14:21,077 --> 00:14:22,597
I don't want my child

188
00:14:23,037 --> 00:14:24,240
to be tainted by

189
00:14:24,770 --> 00:14:26,960
or get involved in
some inheritance war.

190
00:14:29,630 --> 00:14:30,663
I get that.

191
00:14:31,063 --> 00:14:32,384
But if you do that,

192
00:14:32,737 --> 00:14:35,310
won't you be taking away
your child's opportunities?

193
00:14:36,783 --> 00:14:38,200
If you announce

194
00:14:38,257 --> 00:14:40,257
your child is the viscount's,

195
00:14:40,603 --> 00:14:42,090
they'll want for nothing.

196
00:14:42,423 --> 00:14:44,590
Not only your child
will live comfortably,

197
00:14:44,977 --> 00:14:46,720
you will as well.

198
00:14:50,110 --> 00:14:51,240
I know, ma'am.

199
00:14:51,590 --> 00:14:54,763
But opportunities from a war that
will turn this house into hell...

200
00:14:56,610 --> 00:14:58,440
I want nothing to do with it.

201
00:15:07,023 --> 00:15:08,756
I want you to think it through.

202
00:15:09,557 --> 00:15:10,680
For your child's sake.

203
00:15:17,803 --> 00:15:19,283
I've thought it through, ma'am,

204
00:15:19,537 --> 00:15:20,996
You of all people should know

205
00:15:21,243 --> 00:15:23,440
money can corrupt even good people.

206
00:15:32,743 --> 00:15:34,880
After the viscount's funeral,

207
00:15:35,237 --> 00:15:38,920
I'm inviting all of you
to my and Dech's wedding,

208
00:15:41,043 --> 00:15:42,043
It's...

209
00:15:45,320 --> 00:15:49,811
(House of the Dark Shadows
novel: Phakhinai, screenplay: Wannason)

210
00:15:50,293 --> 00:15:54,780
(House of the Dark Shadows
novel: Phakhinai, screenplay: Wannason)

211
00:15:57,500 --> 00:15:58,987
My dear Lordship,

212
00:15:59,310 --> 00:16:01,794
you shouldn't have left me so soon.

213
00:16:02,829 --> 00:16:04,160
My dear Lordship!

214
00:16:09,037 --> 00:16:10,800
My dear Lordship!

215
00:16:12,810 --> 00:16:14,320
- My Lordship!
- Ms. Ramphoei.

216
00:16:14,930 --> 00:16:15,970
Ms. Ramphoei.

217
00:16:17,156 --> 00:16:18,156
Please get up.

218
00:16:18,383 --> 00:16:20,730
So the guests can pay
the viscount their respects.

219
00:16:21,037 --> 00:16:22,434
Uan, you dare order me?

220
00:16:23,023 --> 00:16:24,447
I'm not ordering you.

221
00:16:25,269 --> 00:16:27,320
But it's inappropriate,
Ms. Ramphoei.

222
00:16:27,869 --> 00:16:30,270
Don't you see
the guests are waiting?

223
00:16:30,466 --> 00:16:31,466
Please get up.

224
00:16:37,010 --> 00:16:38,010
Eh?

225
00:16:38,170 --> 00:16:39,170
What's wrong, ma'am?

226
00:16:39,637 --> 00:16:40,964
Did your legs fall asleep?

227
00:16:41,790 --> 00:16:42,790
No.

228
00:16:43,817 --> 00:16:46,200
Where are Dech and Malai?

229
00:16:46,210 --> 00:16:47,817
Why don't I see them?

230
00:16:59,737 --> 00:17:01,160
Don't go yet, Ms. Malai.

231
00:17:03,257 --> 00:17:04,536
We both should get back.

232
00:17:04,790 --> 00:17:06,390
I'm sorry, Ms. Malai,

233
00:17:06,519 --> 00:17:09,140
but I think
you should hear him out.

234
00:17:11,400 --> 00:17:12,640
Please excuse me.

235
00:17:22,877 --> 00:17:24,624
What else do you wanna lie to me?

236
00:17:29,250 --> 00:17:31,193
I never thought of lying to you.

237
00:17:31,203 --> 00:17:32,510
I'm not stupid, Dech.

238
00:17:32,797 --> 00:17:34,687
I can't keep lying to me.

239
00:17:35,237 --> 00:17:36,237
Ms. Malai.

240
00:17:37,457 --> 00:17:38,834
I'm not lying, ma'am.

241
00:17:39,880 --> 00:17:41,774
Are you saying
you weren't with Ramphoei?

242
00:17:42,286 --> 00:17:44,083
Then you're the murderer.

243
00:17:47,716 --> 00:17:48,920
Or do you deny it?

244
00:17:51,237 --> 00:17:52,237
You can't?

245
00:17:53,481 --> 00:17:55,174
Then what do you want me to hear?

246
00:17:55,523 --> 00:17:57,423
Ms. Malai. Ms. Malai.

247
00:17:58,097 --> 00:17:59,587
Trust me, Ms. Malai.

248
00:17:59,597 --> 00:18:01,520
I'd never do such a wicked thing.

249
00:18:02,650 --> 00:18:05,080
- I love...
- You love me.

250
00:18:07,770 --> 00:18:09,960
I've heard it a thousand times.

251
00:18:12,423 --> 00:18:13,423
Honestly,

252
00:18:13,647 --> 00:18:17,087
I'm not sure if your loving words
mean anything anymore.

253
00:18:19,390 --> 00:18:21,160
Please stop pestering me, Dech.

254
00:18:21,577 --> 00:18:24,840
I don't want your words
or even your love.

255
00:18:25,317 --> 00:18:27,720
You two lovebirds are hiding here.

256
00:18:28,937 --> 00:18:30,600
- Ms. Ramphoei.
- Yeah, it's me!

257
00:18:31,937 --> 00:18:32,937
Goodness gracious,

258
00:18:33,177 --> 00:18:34,454
your husband just died

259
00:18:34,464 --> 00:18:36,197
and here you're stealing my man.

260
00:18:38,870 --> 00:18:40,000
Where are you going?

261
00:18:40,210 --> 00:18:41,360
I'm not letting you go.

262
00:18:41,683 --> 00:18:43,560
Let me slap you first,
you mistress.

263
00:18:44,697 --> 00:18:45,697
Ms. Ramphoei,

264
00:18:45,737 --> 00:18:47,480
stop calling her a mistress.

265
00:18:47,490 --> 00:18:48,854
She's not anyone's mistress.

266
00:18:48,864 --> 00:18:50,000
Get that straight.

267
00:18:51,084 --> 00:18:52,084
Let go.

268
00:18:53,124 --> 00:18:54,124
Why can't I?

269
00:18:54,290 --> 00:18:55,843
Since you're my husband.

270
00:18:56,117 --> 00:18:57,343
My son's father.

271
